{"ts":"2026-06-27T11:01:32.927Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Prioritizing Security Implementation**\n\nI've been thinking about the security implementation, and after weighing options, I'm absolutely sold on using Passlib with bcrypt version 3.2.0. The testing went flawlessly, and it's the standard for enterprise-level hashing, so this is the route I'm going to take.\n\n\n**Revising Token Structure**\n\nI'm revisiting the access token structure to ensure it perfectly aligns with the requirements. Specifically, I'm focusing on incorporating \"user_id,\" role, client_id (nullable), and email within the payload. The key is to verify how the existing decoding process in `deps.py` handles the \"sub\" claim and whether the change of email to a sub will work.\n\n\n**Analyzing Token Creation Process**\n\nI'm now diving into the token creation process itself, specifically the `create_access_token` function. I'm taking notes on how the payload is constructed and how the header is being defined. Then I'm thinking about how I'm going to integrate this with the decoding process in `deps.py`. I am thinking about how to retrieve the `email` from the token. I need to write `decode_access_token(token: str) -> Optional[str]` to return the `email` from the token, and also write `get_token_expiry(token: str) -> Optional[datetime]`.\n\n\n**Updating Token Construction**\n\nI've realized a critical issue. The current `create_access_token` call in `auth.py` doesn't pass the necessary user-specific information. I need to update `create_access_token_for_user` to include `user_id`, `role`, and `client_id` in the token payload. This is to ensure all required fields are present in the token.\n\n\n**Refining Token Payload Inclusion**\n\nI've got a solid plan to update `create_access_token_for_user`.  My goal is to incorporate `user_id`, `role`, and `client_id` in the token payload. This is perfect for the login flow. I'm now considering the registration flow as well. The registration will return `UserResponse`, not `Token`. Does a new registration automatically call the login endpoint?\n\n\n**Verifying Decode Functionality**\n\nI'm now carefully verifying the functionality of `decode_access_token` and `get_token_expiry`. I am going to carefully write them, using `security.py`'s `base64url_encode` and `base64url_decode` functions. I need to take a look at the existing `security.py` to make sure I am not re-inventing the wheel. I'm going to leverage the existing custom encoder/decoder for JWT to avoid adding external dependencies. I'll make sure to get all parts of the token.\n\n\n**Expanding Payload Retrieval**\n\nI'm now thinking about retrieving the entire decoded payload, not just the email or the sub. I'll need a way to access other fields within the token. I'm considering implementing `decode_access_token_payload(token: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` to return a dictionary containing the complete payload, or simply returning the payload directly.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T11:01:32.929Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"b48co08t","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/backend/app/core/security.py","old_text":"import hmac\nimport hashlib\nimport base64\nimport json\nimport time\nfrom typing import Dict, Any, Optional\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta\nfrom .config import settings\n\ndef hash_password(password: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Securely hash a password using PBKDF2 HMAC SHA256 with a salt.\n    \"\"\"\n    salt = settings.JWT_SECRET.encode('utf-8')\n    hashed = hashlib.pbkdf2_hmac('sha256', password.encode('utf-8'), salt, 100000)\n    return hashed.hex()\n\ndef verify_password(plain_password: str, hashed_password: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"\n    Verify if a plain password matches its hash.\n    \"\"\"\n    return hash_password(plain_password) == hashed_password\n\ndef base64url_encode(data: bytes) -> str:\n    return base64.urlsafe_b64encode(data).rstrip(b'=').decode('utf-8')\n\ndef base64url_decode(data: str) -> bytes:\n    padding = '=' * (4 - (len(data) % 4))\n    return base64.urlsafe_b64decode(data + padding)\n\ndef create_access_token(subject: str, expires_delta: Optional[timedelta] = None) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Create a secure HS256 JSON Web Token (JWT) using python standard library.\n    \"\"\"\n    if expires_delta:\n        expire = datetime.utcnow() + expires_delta\n    else:\n        expire = datetime.utcnow() + timedelta(minutes=settings.ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES)\n    \n    header = {\"alg\": \"HS256\", \"typ\": \"JWT\"}\n    payload = {\n        \"sub\": str(subject),\n        \"exp\": int(expire.timestamp()),\n        \"iat\": int(datetime.utcnow().timestamp())\n    }\n    \n    header_json = json.dumps(header, separators=(',', ':')).encode('utf-8')\n    payload_json = json.dumps(payload, separators=(',', ':')).encode('utf-8')\n    \n    header_b64 = base64url_encode(header_json)\n    payload_b64 = base64url_encode(payload_json)\n    \n    signing_input = f\"{header_b64}.{payload_b64}\".encode('utf-8')\n    signature = hmac.new(\n        settings.JWT_SECRET.encode('utf-8'),\n        signing_input,\n        hashlib.sha256\n    ).digest()\n    \n    signature_b64 = base64url_encode(signature)\n    return f\"{header_b64}.{payload_b64}.{signature_b64}\"\n\ndef decode_access_token(token: str) -> Optional[str]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Decode and verify a JWT token. Returns the subject (sub) if valid, else None.\n    \"\"\"\n    try:\n        parts = token.split('.')\n        if len(parts) != 3:\n            return None\n        \n        header_b64, payload_b64, signature_b64 = parts\n        \n        # Verify signature\n        signing_input = f\"{header_b64}.{payload_b64}\".encode('utf-8')\n        expected_signature = hmac.new(\n            settings.JWT_SECRET.encode('utf-8'),\n            signing_input,\n            hashlib.sha256\n        ).digest()\n        \n        if not hmac.compare_digest(base64url_decode(signature_b64), expected_signature):\n            return None\n        \n        payload_bytes = base64url_decode(payload_b64)\n        payload = json.loads(payload_bytes.decode('utf-8'))\n        \n        # Check expiration\n        exp = payload.get(\"exp\")\n        if exp is None or time.time() > exp:\n            return None\n            \n        return payload.get(\"sub\")\n    except Exception:\n        return None","new_text":"import hmac\nimport hashlib\nimport base64\nimport json\nimport time\nfrom typing import Dict, Any, Optional\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta\nfrom passlib.context import CryptContext\nfrom .config import settings\n\n# Enterprise-grade secure password hashing context\npwd_context = CryptContext(schemes=[\"bcrypt\"], deprecated=\"auto\")\n\ndef hash_password(password: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Securely hash a password using bcrypt.\n    \"\"\"\n    return pwd_context.hash(password)\n\ndef verify_password(plain_password: str, hashed_password: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"\n    Verify if a plain password matches its hash.\n    \"\"\"\n    try:\n        return pwd_context.verify(plain_password, hashed_password)\n    except Exception:\n        return False\n\ndef base64url_encode(data: bytes) -> str:\n    return base64.urlsafe_b64encode(data).rstrip(b'=').decode('utf-8')\n\ndef base64url_decode(data: str) -> bytes:\n    padding = '=' * (4 - (len(data) % 4))\n    return base64.urlsafe_b64decode(data + padding)\n\ndef create_access_token(\n    subject: str,\n    user_id: Optional[int] = None,\n    role: Optional[str] = None,\n    client_id: Optional[int] = None,\n    email: Optional[str] = None,\n    expires_delta: Optional[timedelta] = None\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Create a secure HS256 JSON Web Token (JWT) containing user_id, role, client_id, and email.\n    \"\"\"\n    if expires_delta:\n        expire = datetime.utcnow() + expires_delta\n    else:\n        expire = datetime.utcnow() + timedelta(minutes=settings.ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES)\n    \n    header = {\"alg\": \"HS256\", \"typ\": \"JWT\"}\n    payload = {\n        \"sub\": str(subject),\n        \"user_id\": user_id,\n        \"role\": role,\n        \"client_id\": client_id,\n        \"email\": email or subject,\n        \"exp\": int(expire.timestamp()),\n        \"iat\": int(datetime.utcnow().timestamp())\n    }\n    \n    header_json = json.dumps(header, separators=(',', ':')).encode('utf-8')\n    payload_json = json.dumps(payload, separators=(',', ':')).encode('utf-8')\n    \n    header_b64 = base64url_encode(header_json)\n    payload_b64 = base64url_encode(payload_json)\n    \n    signing_input = f\"{header_b64}.{payload_b64}\".encode('utf-8')\n    signature = hmac.new(\n        settings.JWT_SECRET.encode('utf-8'),\n        signing_input,\n        hashlib.sha256\n    ).digest()\n    \n    signature_b64 = base64url_encode(signature)\n    return f\"{header_b64}.{payload_b64}.{signature_b64}\"\n\ndef decode_access_token(token: str) -> Optional[str]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Decode and verify a JWT token. Returns the subject/email if valid, else None.\n    \"\"\"\n    try:\n        parts = token.split('.')\n        if len(parts) != 3:\n            return None\n        \n        header_b64, payload_b64, signature_b64 = parts\n        \n        # Verify signature\n        signing_input = f\"{header_b64}.{payload_b64}\".encode('utf-8')\n        expected_signature = hmac.new(\n            settings.JWT_SECRET.encode('utf-8'),\n            signing_input,\n            hashlib.sha256\n        ).digest()\n        \n        if not hmac.compare_digest(base64url_decode(signature_b64), expected_signature):\n            return None\n        \n        payload_bytes = base64url_decode(payload_b64)\n        payload = json.loads(payload_bytes.decode('utf-8'))\n        \n        # Check expiration\n        exp = payload.get(\"exp\")\n        if exp is None or time.time() > exp:\n            return None\n            \n        return payload.get(\"email\") or payload.get(\"sub\")\n    except Exception:\n        return None\n\ndef decode_access_token_payload(token: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Decode and return the full validated payload of a JWT token, or None if invalid.\n    \"\"\"\n    try:\n        parts = token.split('.')\n        if len(parts) != 3:\n            return None\n        \n        header_b64, payload_b64, signature_b64 = parts\n        \n        # Verify signature\n        signing_input = f\"{header_b64}.{payload_b64}\".encode('utf-8')\n        expected_signature = hmac.new(\n            settings.JWT_SECRET.encode('utf-8'),\n            signing_input,\n            hashlib.sha256\n        ).digest()\n        \n        if not hmac.compare_digest(base64url_decode(signature_b64), expected_signature):\n            return None\n        \n        payload_bytes = base64url_decode(payload_b64)\n        payload = json.loads(payload_bytes.decode('utf-8'))\n        \n        # Check expiration\n        exp = payload.get(\"exp\")\n        if exp is None or time.time() > exp:\n            return None\n            \n        return payload\n    except Exception:\n        return None\n\ndef get_token_expiry(token: str) -> Optional[datetime]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Decode a JWT token and return its expiry datetime if valid.\n    \"\"\"\n    try:\n        parts = token.split('.')\n        if len(parts) != 3:\n            return None\n        \n        header_b64, payload_b64, signature_b64 = parts\n        \n        # Verify signature\n        signing_input = f\"{header_b64}.{payload_b64}\".encode('utf-8')\n        expected_signature = hmac.new(\n            settings.JWT_SECRET.encode('utf-8'),\n            signing_input,\n            hashlib.sha256\n        ).digest()\n        \n        if not hmac.compare_digest(base64url_decode(signature_b64), expected_signature):\n            return None\n        \n        payload_bytes = base64url_decode(payload_b64)\n        payload = json.loads(payload_bytes.decode('utf-8'))\n        \n        exp = payload.get(\"exp\")\n        if exp is None:\n            return None\n            \n        return datetime.utcfromtimestamp(exp)\n    except Exception:\n        return None\n"}}}
